As the world celebrates International Women’s Day (IWD), an Abuja based nongovernmental organization, Helpline Foundation for the Needy, has called on women to be economically viable aimed at forging a more gender-balanced world. The group, also revealed that the 2019 edition of International Women’s Day, will be used to examine women’s achievements and challenges with a view to creating gender parity. Addressing a world press conference in Abuja to mark the occasion, President of Helpline Foundation for the Needy, Dr. Jumai Ahmadu called for collective efforts and shared ownership for driving gender equality “As we speak, every March 8 is a great and important time in history to do everything possible to help forge a more gender-balanced world. Women have come a long way, yet there’s still more to be achieved. The story of women’s struggle for equality belongs to no single person or gender nor to any one organization but to the collective efforts of all who care about human rights,” Ahmadu stressed. Speaking on this year theme; “Balance for Better”, she described the theme as a call to action for driving gender balance across the world, while calling on women not to see themselves as weaker vessels.  Gender dynamics at INEC Int’l Girl Child Day: Group tasks govt on skill programmes NGO advocates gender balance for girl-child